data.name: ItAllStarted
data.value: It all started with the immune system. Over forty years ago, scientists based in Montreal, Canada, discovered the role of a specially-prepared whey protein isolate (now famous as Immunocal) in raising glutathione, a molecule often referred to as the body's master antioxidant. By the mid-1990s, the scientists had teamed up with veteran network marketing entrepreneur, Chuck Roberts, Dieter Beer, and John Molson, of the notable Canadian Molson family, to found the company now known to the world as Immunotec.

data.name: Milestone01
data.value: Immunotec transitions from public to private company under the leadership of Mauricio Domenzain.

data.name: Milestone02
data.value: Immunotec is recognized as a Top 100 Direct Selling company worldwide in 2017 and 2015.

data.name: Milestone03
data.value: Immunotec launches its brand evolution featuring a new logo and new tagline: "The Science of Living Better".

data.name: Milestone04
data.value: Immunotec launches Cogniva, a product on the new frontier in brain health.

data.name: Milestone05
data.value: Immunotec enters the skin care market with the launch of the Elasense Skin Care line.

data.name: Milestone06
data.value: Immunotec receives regulatory approval to market Immunocal with the health claim: "Helps increase muscle strength and enhance performance when combined with regular exercise."

data.name: Milestone07
data.value: Immunocal and Immunocal Platinum are certified by the anti-doping laboratory LGC and granted the "Informed-Choice Trusted by sport" logo.

data.name: Milestone08
data.value: Immunotec is recognized as a Top 50 direct selling company in Canada and the U.S. and a Top 2 in Canada.

data.name: Milestone09
data.value: Immunotec named sponsor of Rowing Canada.

data.name: Milestone10
data.value: Immunotec launches the MiForm Weight Management System.

data.name: Milestone11
data.value: Glutathione research papers surpass 100,000 articles on PubMed.

data.name: Milestone12
data.value: Immunotec opens new office in Mexico City.

data.name: Milestone13
data.value: Immunocal first appears in Canadian Compendium of Pharmaceuticals and Specialties (CPS).

data.name: Milestone14
data.value: Immunocal is certified free of prohibited substances based on the 2007 World Anti‑Doping Code Prohibited List.

data.name: Milestone15
data.value: Immunotec receives approval to market Immunocal with the health claim: "A natural source of the glutathione precursor cysteine for the maintenance of a strong immune system."

data.name: Milestone16
data.value: Dr. Dröge launches Immunocal Platinum, the next generation of Immunocal with CMP and RMF.

data.name: Milestone17
data.value: World renowned immunologist, Dr. Wulf Dröge, joins Immunotec as Senior VP, Research and Development.

data.name: Milestone18
data.value: Immunotec moves to new 37,000 sq. ft. headquarters and 1,000 Consultants celebrate.

data.name: Milestone19
data.value: The first Immunotec Consultant earns a million dollars.

data.name: Milestone20
data.value: Immunocal listed in the highly respected U.S. Physicians' Desk Reference (PDR).

data.name: Milestone21
data.value: Dr. Larry Lands publishes first paper on Immunocal and sports performance.

data.name: Milestone22
data.value: Official launch of HMS 90 (Immunocal) in Canada in 1996. Official launch of Immunocal in the U.S. in 1997.

data.name: Milestone23
data.value: Immunotec Research Corp. merges with Chuck Roberts' company to form Immunotec Research Ltd. with John Molson as founding shareholder.

data.name: Milestone24
data.value: Dr. Gustavo Bounous and Dieter Beer initiate close association. Launch Immunotec Research Corp.

data.name: Milestone25
data.value: Dr. Wulf Dröge describes the effect of glutathione on the immune response of a living organism.

data.name: Milestone26
data.value: Dr. Gustavo Bounous and Dr. Patricia Kongshavn are the first to discover the effect of whey protein on the immune system.

data.name: Milestone27
data.value: Dr. Gustavo Bounous initiated a novel research program in conjunction with colleagues, including Dr. Patricia Kongshavn, to search for a dietary protein source that would optimize the immune system.
